            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> cold coastlines or plains<br/><b>Organization</b> solitary or pair<br/><b>Treasure</b> none"
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Dire polar bears, kin to cave bears, are larger and more aggressive than cave bears and normal polar bears alike. These short-tempered animals tend to avoid settled regions, but sometimes venture dangerously close to them while hunting, potentially resulting in bloody massacres."
        }
    ],
